                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 3691/494.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">Chargé <persName type="from">Brown</persName> to the <gloss
                            type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>.</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.—Paraphrase.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">American Legation</hi>,<lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Amapala</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1907-04-24">
                            <hi rend="italic">April 24, 1907</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Reports that the treaty of peace and amity which has been signed is similar to
                    the <hi rend="italic">Marblehead</hi> treaty, and includes provision for a
                    Central American Peace Congress in Nicaragua and a special commercial treaty
                    between the two Republics. Adds that the friendly mediation of the United States
                    is gratefully acknowledged by both countries.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
